# Code Formatting Standards

## TRIGGER
ALWAYS ACTIVE - Apply these formatting rules to all code generated.

## RULES

### Indentation
- Use 4 spaces for indentation (not tabs)
- Consistent indentation across all file types

### Line Length
- Maximum line length: 120 characters
- Break long lines at logical points

### Naming Conventions
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., getUserData)
- Classes: PascalCase (e.g., UserController)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., MAX_RETRY_COUNT)
- Private fields: _camelCase with underscore prefix

### Comments
- Use single-line comments for brief explanations
- Use multi-line comments for complex logic
- No commented-out code in final commits

### Code Organization
- Group related functions together
- Place private methods below public methods
- Keep files under 300 lines when possible
